{"build_type":"library","description":"The supervisor event loop, zero sleeps. Builds a two-entry pollfd watching the signal descriptor (context slot 2) and the backoff timer descriptor (context slot 3) for readability, blocks in poll with timeout minus one (wait forever for an event), then dispatches: if the signal descriptor is readable the managed service died, run the death handler; if the timer descriptor is readable the backoff elapsed, run the restart handler. Then tail-recurse to wait for the next event. Each branch body is a single call so per-branch temporaries stay independent.","module_name":"dispatch-supervisor-events-until-process-terminated","package_name":"dispatch-supervisor-events-until-process-terminated","function_definitions":{"dispatch-supervisor-events-until-process-terminated":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"ctx","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"six","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":6},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"twelve","variable_type":"i64